Male New Artist\n| Ateez\n| {{Nom}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://promotion.genie.co.kr/promotion/mgmavotea|title=The Male New Artist|access-date=2019-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190621113859/https://promotion.genie.co.kr/promotion/mgmavotea|archive-date=2019-06-21|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Mnet Asian Music Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; table-layout:fixed; margin-right:0\"\n! Year\n! Award\n! Recipient\n! Result\n! Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2019\n| Artist of the Year\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Ateez\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mama.mwave.me/en/vote|title=MAMA 2019 Awards|access-date=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n|-\n| Worldwide Fans' Choice\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best New Male Artist\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n===MTV EMA Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; table-layout:fixed; margin-right:0\"\n! Year\n! Award\n! Recipient\n! Result\n! Ref\n|-\n| 2019\n| Best Korean Act\n| Ateez\n| {{win}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mtvema.com/en-gb/articles/31m1fd/these-are-the-big-winners-at-the-2019-mtv-ema|title=These are the big winners at the 2019 MTV EMA|access-date=2019-11-04}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Soribada Best K-Music Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; table-layout:fixed; margin-right:0\"\n! Year\n! Award\n! Recipient\n! Result\n! Ref\n|-\n| 2019\n| Best Performance Award\n| Ateez\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1347366wpp/winners-of-day-1-of-2019-soribada-best-k-music-awards|title=Winners Of Day 1 Of 2019 Soribada Best K-Music Awards|work=Soompi.com|access-date=August 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website| http://ateez.kqent.com}} {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:ATEEZ}}\n[[Category:K-pop music groups]]\n[[Category:South Korean boy bands]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2018]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop music groups]]\n[[Category:KQ Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:MTV EMA winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean pop music group}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Ateez\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = 191008 \uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988, '\uba4b\uc9c0\ub2e4' \uac10\ud0c4\ub9cc \ub098\uc624\ub294 \ub2e8\uccb4 \ud3ec\ud1a0\ud0c0\uc784 (ATEEZ 'TREASURE EP FIN All To Action' \uc1fc\ucf00\uc774\uc2a4) 3m10s.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = yes\n| caption          = Ateez at its ''[[Treasure EP.Fin: All to Action]]'' showcase, October 2019 (from left: Yunho, Seonghwa, San, Yeosang, Hongjoong, Wooyoung, Jongho, and Mingi)\n| origin           = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| genre            = [[K-pop]], [[J-pop]]\n| years_active     = 2018\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n*KQ\n*[[Legacy Recordings|Legacy]]\n*[[RCA Records|RCA]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-et-ms-kpop-monsta-x-major-labels-20190703-story.html|title=American record biz goes all-in on K-Pop, but crossover challenges remain|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=July 3, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"billboardexclusive\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/8523607/ateez-signs-rca-records|title=K-Pop Group ATEEZ Signs With RCA Records: Exclusive|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=2019-07-24}}</ref>\n*[[Nippon Columbia]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://columbia.jp/artists/index_a.html|title=Artists|access-date=2019-11-04}}</ref>}}\n| website          = * {{URL|http://ateez.kqent.com}}\n* {{URL|https://ateez-official.jp}}\n| current_members  = * Hongjoong \n* Seonghwa\n* Yunho\n* Yeosang\n* San\n* Mingi\n* Wooyoung \n* Jongho\n}}\n\n'''Ateez''' ({{Korean|hangul=\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988}}, pronounced \"Ei-Teez\"), is an 8-member boy group from South Korea under the company KQ Entertainment.  The group is composed of eight members: Hongjoong, Seonghwa, Yunho, Yeosang, San, Mingi, Wooyoung and Jongho. They debuted on October 24, 2018 with ''[[Treasure EP.1: All to Zero]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2018/09/new-boy-group-ateez-from-block-bs-agency-to-make-their-official-debut|title=New boy group ATEEZ from Block B's agency to make their official debut|work=allkpop|access-date=September 29, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/ATEEZofficial/status/1047049457798451206|title=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988) on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=October 4, 2018}}</ref> On November 2, 2018, the group performed their song \"Pirate King\" on [[KBS2]]'s ''Music Bank''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1256511wpp/watch-exo-izone-monsta-x-and-more-perform-on-music-bank|title=Watch: MONSTA X Takes 4th Win For \"Shoot Out\" On \"Music Bank,\" Performances By EXO, IZ*ONE, And More|website=Soompi|language=en-US|access-date=November 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Music Bank K-Chart|url=https://www.viki.com/tv/35526|language=en|access-date=November 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n===2018: Pre-debut and ''Treasure EP.1: All to Zero''===\nPrior to their debut, Ateez were called KQ Fellaz<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2018/11/07/have-you-heard-ateez-kq-fellaz|title=Have You Hear Of: ATEEZ (KQ Fellaz)|website=SBS PopAsia HQ|date=7 November 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> after their label, KQ Entertainment. KQ Entertainment released a YouTube series, ''KQ Fellaz American Training'' in which they traveled to [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]] to train. During this show, KQ Entertainment introduced a ninth member to the trainee group, Lee Junyoung.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2018/11/07/have-you-heard-ateez-kq-fellaz|title=Have You Heard Of: ATEEZ (KQ Fellaz)|website=SBS PopAsia|language=en|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref> Together, they composed and choreographed a song, produced by the leader Hongjoong, and trained at dance studios Movement Lifestyle<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AhOXA5Rq6p8|title=KQ Fellaz \ubbf8\uad6d \uc5f0\uc218\uae30 EP. 6|website=youtube.com|date=2018-05-29}}</ref> and [[The Millennium Dance Complex|Millennium Dance Complex]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nkwWsWISnJ0|title=KQ Fellaz \ubbf8\uad6d \uc5f0\uc218\uae30 EP. 9|website=youtube.com|date=2018-06-05}}</ref> Yunho was also featured in one of Millennium's dance videos.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DFjIH12wauQ|title=Usher \u2013 Take You There -Choreography By FeFe Burgos|website=youtube.com|date=2018-02-26}}</ref> The group released their first performance video on May 18. Through this release, KQ Entertainment announced that trainee Lee Junyoung would not join the final debut team. For the finale of the YouTube series, KQ Fellaz released the song, \"From\", on July 3, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F-89J5Qu3r0|title=KQ Fellaz EP. Final - From (Made by KQ Fellaz)|website=youtube.com|date=2018-07-02}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the YouTube Series, KQ Entertainment announced KQ Fellaz's reality show on June 26, 2018, with the first of three teasers. The second teaser was released on July 3, in which they introduced the official name for the group: Ateez. Hence, the reality show was ultimately called ''Code Name is Ateez''. The third teaser was uploaded on July 13, showcasing the show's opening title. The show premiered on the Korean broadcasting media [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]] on July 20.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/PlayMnet|title=Code Name Is ATEEZ|website=youtube|access-date=2019-07-24}}</ref>\n\nOn October 2, 2018, through their official SNS, Ateez released a teaser photo announcing their debut date. Additionally, it provided of the date and location of their debut showcase: October 24 in Yes24 Livehall.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ATEEZofficial/status/1047049457798451206|title=[] ATEEZ Hot Debut \u2013 Will You Be My Friend? \u2013 2018. 10. 24 \u2013 #ATEEZ #\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988pic.twitter.com/x1XvzWCmQs|last=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988)|date=2018-10-02|website=@ATEEZofficial|language=en|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref> Following this announcement, they sequentially uploaded teaser photos from October 8 to October 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://officiallykmusic.com/ateezs-yeosang-carries-flag-new-teasers-treasure-ep-1-zero/|title=ATEEZ's Yeosang carries on the flag in new teasers for 'Treasure Ep.1: All to Zero' \u22c6 The latest kpop news and music {{!}} Officially Kmusic|date=2018-10-15|website=The latest kpop news and music {{!}} Officially Kmusic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://officiallykmusic.com/ateez-release-next-batch-teasers-featuring-seonghwa-yunho/|title=ATEEZ release next batch of teasers featuring Seonghwa and Yunho \u22c6 The latest kpop news and music {{!}} Officially Kmusic|date=2018-10-15|website=The latest kpop news and music {{!}} Officially Kmusic|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref> On October 24, 2018, Ateez released their debut [[Extended play|EP]], ''[[Treasure EP.1: All to Zero]]''.<ref>{{Citation|title=TREASURE EP.1: All to Zero by ATEEZ|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/treasure-ep-1-all-to-zero/1439301204|language=en-us|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref> Alongside the release of the album were music videos for titles tracks, \"Pirate King\" and \"Treasure\". The album reached #7 on the [[Gaon Album Chart|Gaon Albums Chart]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=43&hitYear=2018&termGbn=week|title=2018\ub144 43\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart|access-date=2019-07-10}}</ref> The group held their debut showcase in the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ATEEZofficial/status/1050687532197789696|title=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988) Debut Showcase \ud2f0\ucf13 \uc624\ud508 \uc548\ub0b4|language=ko|work=Twitter|date=October 12, 2018|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref> Their first music show performance was on October 25 on Mnet's ''[[M Countdown]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KAXWhITwJp8|title=[ATEEZ - Pirate King] Debut Stage (M COUNTDOWN 181025 EP.593)|work=YouTube|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2019: ''Treasure EP.2'', ''Treasure EP.3'', ''Treasure EP.Fin'', The Expedition Tour and Debut in Japan===\nOn January 2, Ateez released an image through their official SNS with Morse code as the caption. They later confirmed their comeback EP, ''[[Treasure EP.2: Zero to One]]'', on January 3 with a follow up teaser.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2019/01/ateez-begin-teasing-for-their-first-comeback-since-debut-with-a-mystery-image-morse-code|title=ATEEZ begin teasing for their first comeback since debut with a mystery image + morse code|website=allkpop|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref> On January 15, they released ''Treasure EP.2: Zero to One'' alongside the music video for the lead single \"Say My Name\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kqent.com/producer/1594|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988|website=KQ\uc5d4\ud130\ud14c\uc778\uba3c\ud2b8|language=ko-KR|access-date=2019-01-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nKU4OVH18mE|title=YouTube|website=youtube.com|access-date=2019-01-15}}</ref> The performance video of \"Hala Hala (Hearts Awakened, Live Alive)\" was released on February 7.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QbjmVyP9RFg|title=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988) - 'HALA HALA (Hearts Awakened, Live Alive)' Official MV (Performance ver.)|website=youtube.com|date=2019-02-07}}</ref> On January 24, they announced their first ever tour, titled The Expedition Tour, with March tour dates in Brooklyn, Chicago, Dallas, Atlanta, and Los Angeles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8494942/k-pop-boy-band-ateez-announce-us-tour|title=K-Pop Boy Band ATEEZ Announce U.S. Tour|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref> All dates were sold out.<ref>https://www.chicagotribune.com/travel/sns-201903120002--tms--celebtrvctnct-a20190312-20190312-story.html</ref><ref name=\"billboardexclusive\"/>\n\nOn February 20, they announced more tour dates for Europe, with April shows in London, Lisbon, Paris, Berlin, Amsterdam, Milan, Budapest, Stockholm, Warsaw, and Moscow.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/_mymusictaste/status/1098160376192159744|title=Get ready for Ateez \u2013 The Expedition Tour in EUROPE!|last=MyMusicTaste|date=2019-02-20|website=@_mymusictaste|language=en|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref> All shows were reported to be sold out.<ref>http://www.mtv.com/news/3119026/ateez-tour-interview-performance/</ref><ref name=\"forbes2\"/>\n\nOn May 9, the music video for \"Promise\" was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ukbr7xyPoRQ|title=YouTube|website=youtube.com|access-date=2019-07-07}}</ref> On May 17, Ateez performed at [[KCON (music festival)|KCON 2019 Japan]] in Chiba, Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kconjapan.com/mcountdown/lineup/|title=KCON 2019 Japan X M Countdown Line Up|access-date=2019-07-07}}</ref>\n\nOn June 5, Ateez announced their first tour of Australia, titled The Expedition Tour In Australia, with shows scheduled in Melbourne on August 9 at Margaret Court Arena and Sydney on August 11 at The Big Top Sydney. The band released their third EP, ''[[Treasure EP.3: One to All]]'' on June 10.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ATEEZofficial/status/1135108852733472768?s=20|title=[] ATEEZ TREASURE EP.3 : One To All Concept Photo '\uc0b0(SAN)' ALBUM RELEASE 2019. 6. 10 6PM #One_To_All #WAVE #ATEEZ #\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988 #\uc0b0 #SANpic.twitter.com/ITfTA5Zod0|last=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988)|date=2019-06-02|website=@ATEEZofficial|language=en|access-date=2020-01-11}}</ref> The lead single from the EP, \"Wave\", was selected via a fan vote.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffbenjamin/2019/06/13/ateez-treasure-ep3-all-to-one-wave-illusion-fan-vote-decided-new-single/#219f25d642ee|title=ATEEZ Release New EP After More Than 600,000 Fan Votes Decided Their New Single|date=June 13, 2019|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|accessdate=June 16, 2019|work=[[Forbes]]}}</ref> On the same day, the music video of \"Wave\" and \"Illusion\" were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FIInyEWWW-s|title=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988) - 'WAVE' Official MV|website=youtube.com|date=2019-07-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i_HzsHss94E|title=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988) - 'ILLUSION' Official MV|website=youtube.com|date=2019-07-08}}</ref> On June 20, Ateez won their first music program broadcast award on [[M Countdown]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://post.naver.com/viewer/postView.nhn?volumeNo=21591012&memberNo=24876555|title=190620 \uc5e0\uce74\uc6b4\ud2b8\ub2e4\uc6b4 \uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988(ATEEZ) \u2013 WAVE 1\uc704 \uc575\ucf5c \ud604\uc7a5\ud3ec\ud1a0}}</ref> On June 25, they won their second music program broadcast award, 1st Place The Show Choice Winner on [[The Show (South Korean TV series)|The Show]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.mk.co.kr/view.php?year=2019&no=455839|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988 '\ub354\uc1fc' 1\uc704, SF9-\uc6b0\uc8fc\uc18c\ub140 \uc774\uacbc\ub2e4}}</ref>\n\nOn July 6, Ateez performed at [[KCON (music festival)|KCON 2019 NY]] in New York City, USA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kconusa.com/kcon-ny-artists|title=KCON 2019 NY Line Up|access-date=2019-07-07}}</ref> On July 8, the music video for \"Aurora\" was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7wcM9Eq3UbI|title=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988) - 'AURORA' Official MV (Performance ver.)|website=youtube.com|date=2019-07-08}}</ref> Aurora was written, composed and produced by leader Hongjoong. On August 16, Ateez participated in and performed at KCON Rookies, which was part of KCON LA.\n\nOn August 17, Ateez performed at the KCON 2019 concert in [[Los Angeles]]. On August 19, Ateez also performed at the KCON LA After Party. On August 20, Ateez received their first music award Best Performance Award at Soribada Awards 2019.\n\nOn September 18, Ateez announced their comeback with ''[[Treasure EP.Fin: All to Action]]''. A series of photo and video teasers were released for the album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ATEEZofficial/status/1174156139656646656|title=[] ATEEZ NOW READY FOR NEXT JOURNEY #ATEEZ #\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988pic.twitter.com/Eg9sPEQj3s|last=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988)|date=2019-09-17|website=@ATEEZofficial|language=en|access-date=2019-09-18}}</ref> They performed at KCON Thailand on September 29.\n\nOn October 4, Ateez performed at Spotify On Stage 2019 in Jakarta, Indonesia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spotifyonstage.com/jkt/lineup/ateez|title=Spotify On Stage Line Up|access-date=2019-10-04}}</ref> On October 6, they performed at Seoul Music Festival (SMUF).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://seoulmusicfestival.com|title=Seoul Music Festival|access-date=2019-10-06}}</ref> On October 8, Ateez released their first full studio album, ''Treasure EP.Fin: All to Action''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/bbs/board.php?bo_table=news&wr_id=95|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988, \ubbff\uace0 \ubcf4\ub294 \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 \uc815\uc11d\u2025\ubcc0\uc2e0 \uc7a5\ub974\ub4e4\uc758 \uc644\uacb0\ud310 '\uc6d0\ub354\ub79c\ub4dc' KQ ENT. 116\ud68c|access-date=2019-10-08}}</ref> The music video of the title song \"Wonderland\" was also released on the same day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z_BhMhZpAug|title=ATEEZ(\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988) - 'WONDERLAND' Official MV|website=youtube.com|access-date=2019-10-08}}</ref> They performed at Busan One Asia Festival on October 20.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3XUG1NKy-Wk|title=ATEEZ (\uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988) - WONDERLAND [2019 BOF 191020]|website=youtube.com|access-date=2019-10-24}}</ref>\n\nOn November 2, Ateez performed at Jindai Festa in Yokohama, Japan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jindaifesta.com/project|title=\u4f01\u753b|access-date=2019-11-04}}</ref> On November 10, the MV of Ateez's Japanese debut title song \"Utopia\" was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZLQm-8Z6C8M|website=youtube.com|title=ATEEZ - 'UTOPIA (Japanese Ver.)' Official Music Video|access-date=2019-11-10}}</ref>\n\nOn December 4, Ateez performed at Mnet Asian Music Awards 2019 in Nagoya, Japan, where they received Worldwide Fan Choice top 10 award. On the same day, Ateez released their Japanese debut album ''Treasure EP.Extra: Shift the Map''.\n\n===2020: ''Treasure Epilogue''===\nOn January 6, Ateez released their fourth EP, ''[[Treasure Epilogue: Action to Answer]]'', the final part of the ''Treasure'' series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/609/0000223845|title='\ud56b\ub8e8\ud0a4' \uc5d0\uc774\ud2f0\uc988, 1\uc6d46\uc77c \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4 \ud655\uc815(\uacf5\uc2dd)|date=2019-12-26|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2019-12-25}}</ref> The MV for their title track \"Answer\" was released on the same day. The Japanese MV version of \"Answer\" was released on January 29.\n\nAteez were scheduled to begin their European tour in March 2020. Several stops including Amsterdam, Madrid and Moscow had previously been reported to be sold out since January.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/live/8547884/ateez-add-tickets-world-tour</ref> However due to concerns over [[coronavirus pandemic]] the European dates had been cancelled.<ref>https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/11/ateez-cancel-european-dates-fellowship-map-treasure-tour-amid-fears-coronavirus-12382743//<ref/>\n\n==Members==\nList of members names and positions.\n* Kim Hong-joong (\uae40\ud64d\uc911), leader, rap, composition<!-- \ud3ec\uc9c0\uc158(\ud2b9\uae30) : \ub9ac\ub354, \ub7a9, \uc791\uace1 --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/profile_view.php?id=3|title=Kim Hong Joong|author=|date=|work=Ateez official website|publisher=KQ Entertainment|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* Park Seong-hwa (\ubc15\uc131\ud654), vocal<!-- \ud3ec\uc9c0\uc158(\ud2b9\uae30) : \ubcf4\uceec --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/profile_view.php?id=5|title=Park Seong Hwa|author=|date=|work=Ateez official website|publisher=KQ Entertainment|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* Jeong Yun-ho (\uc815\uc724\ud638), performance, vocal<!-- \ud3ec\uc9c0\uc158(\ud2b9\uae30) : \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4, \ubcf4\uceec --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/profile_view.php?id=6|title=Jeong Yun Ho|author=|date=|work=Ateez official website|publisher=KQ Entertainment|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* Kang Yeo-sang (\uac15\uc5ec\uc0c1), vocal, performance<!-- \ud3ec\uc9c0\uc158(\ud2b9\uae30) : \ubcf4\uceec, \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/profile_view.php?id=7|title=Kang Yeo Sang|author=|date=|work=Ateez official website|publisher=KQ Entertainment|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* Choi San (\ucd5c\uc0b0), vocal<!-- \ud3ec\uc9c0\uc158(\ud2b9\uae30) : \ubcf4\uceec --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/profile_view.php?id=8|title=Choi San|author=|date=|work=Ateez official website|publisher=KQ Entertainment|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* Song Min-gi (\uc1a1\ubbfc\uae30), rap, performance<!-- \ud3ec\uc9c0\uc158(\ud2b9\uae30) : \ub7a9, \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/profile_view.php?id=9|title=Song Min Gi|author=|date=|work=Ateez official website|publisher=KQ Entertainment|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* Jung Woo-young (\uc815\uc6b0\uc601), performance, vocal<!-- \ud3ec\uc9c0\uc158(\ud2b9\uae30) : \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4, \ubcf4\uceec --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/profile_view.php?id=10|title=Jung Woo Young|author=|date=|work=Ateez official website|publisher=KQ Entertainment|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* Choi Jong-ho (\ucd5c\uc885\ud638), main vocal<!-- \ud3ec\uc9c0\uc158(\ud2b9\uae30) : \uba54\uc778\ubcf4\uceec --><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ateez.kqent.com/profile_view.php?id=11|title=Choi Jong Ho|author=|date=|work=Ateez official website|publisher=KQ Entertainment|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected chart positions and sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\" | Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"6\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Gaon Album Chart|KOR]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=41&hitYear=2019&termGbn=week|title=''Treasure EP.Fin: All to Action'' \u2013 Week 41, 2019|website=[[Gaon Music Chart|Gaon Chart]]|language=ko|accessdate=October 17, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[ARIA Digital Album Chart|AUS<br>Dig.]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cdn.aria.com.au/pdfs/867E431A56E5A013B749BB981371C077B6FCF918C16E191882CCF2B41888FAD7/ARIA%20Digital%20Albums%20Chart.pdf?seq=26|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Digital Albums|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=October 14, 2019|accessdate=October 12, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA Dig.]]<br /><ref>France Digital Albums:\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-albums-telecharges/?ye=2019&we=41|title=''Treasure EP.Fin: All to Action - The 1st Album'' (2019)|date=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Oricon Albums Chart|JPN]]<br /><ref>Oricon Albums Chart:\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2019-12-16/|title=''Treasure EP.Extra: Shift the Map'' (2019)|date=December 16, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Top Heatseekers|US<br>Heat.]]<br><ref name=\"heat\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/ateez/chart-history/TLN|title=Ateez Chart History: Heatseeker Albums|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard charts#Albums|US<br>World]]<br><ref name=\"wlp\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/ateez/chart-history/WLP|title=Ateez Chart History: World Albums|website=Billboard|access-date=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Treasure EP.Fin: All to Action]]''\n|\n* Released: October 8, 2019 <small>(KOR)</small>\n* Label: KQ Entertainment, [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n* Formats: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]], [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| 1 || 32 || 53 || \u2014 || 10 || 7\n|\n* KOR: 174,855<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=2019&hitYear=2019&termGbn=year|title=2019\ub144 Album Chart (see #35)|website=Gaon Chart|accessdate=January 10, 2020|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=01&hitYear=2020&termGbn=month|title=2020\ub144 01\uc6d4 Album Chart (see #22)|website=Gaon Chart|accessdate=February 9, 2020|language=ko}}</ref>\n* US: 1,000<ref name=\"wonderland\">{{cite web|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|title=ATEEZ Earn New Peak on World Digital Song Sales Chart With 'Wonderland'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8533403/ateez-wonderland-new-peak-on-world-digital-song-sales-chart|website=Billboard|access-date=October 17, 2019|date=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Treasure EP.Extra: Shift 